<font color="#FF0000">LOVE AND RESPECT</font><br>
<tt>Sat Dec 21 13:35:47 US/Eastern 1996
</tt><p>
Today. The aging veterans of both sides of the Vietnam War greet each other as brothers. Learn a lesson from them. If the men who tried to kill each other in the Vietnam War can reach an understanding of respect and even love in some cases, why can't we? The war is over. In less than two generations the Vietnam war will be just be another part of history. If we could only leave our memories of the past behind as we race into the future, we would all be better off. I don't believe that if we refuse to learn from history we are condemned to relive it. I believe that it is not in our nature to learn from history. Example: If the former Soviet Union had learned from our mistakes,they never would have suffered from their little adventure in Afghanistan.<br>
The little children play in the sun. Our time is done. The world belongs to them now. Let's try to to concentrate on the present environment so that our children have at least a fighting chance in the future.
